SLS: stands for "System-Level Service", which contains a series of functionalities that supports the entire system

The SLS may include or support below functions
-- Transaction
-- Performance monitoring
-- Object pool management
-- Cache management
-- Security service
-- etc.

These functions work as aspects in Spring, hence AOP configuration for SLS is necessary.

Note:
-- When multiple advice from different aspects serve the same target, the advice follow FILO principle

